umented in the risk assessment."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective collaboration between engineering, security, and management teams is essential for addressing security issues and making informed decisions.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI Matrix for ICS Security","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Identify and assess security issues, recommend mitigation actions."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Implement mitigation actions, such as disabling or removing features."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Approve mitigation actions based on risk assessments."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A documented escalation process where unresolved conflicts between engineering and security teams are reviewed by a governance committee for final decision."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"To adapt to evolving threats and incorporate lessons learned from incidents and audits.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor threat intelligence","description":"Regularly review CISA alerts and other sources for new ICS vulnerabilities."},{"step":"Review audit findings","description":"Incorporate findings from internal and external audits into the security issue management process."},{"step":"Update policies","description":"Revise policies and procedures based on new threat intelligence and lessons learned."}],"lessons_learned":"After a security incident involving a legacy PLC, the policy was updated to include mandatory compensating controls for all legacy systems that cannot meet modern security standards."}},"standard_compliance":"IEC 62443-4-1","last_updated":"2023-10-15"} 
